FBIS4-63851 "drsov101_a_94052" FBIS-SOV-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Russians Win Contract to Modernize Indian MiG's Russians Win Contract to Modernize Indian MiG's PM2505083994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 24 May 94 First Edition p 3 PM2505083994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Report from ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS roundup under the rubric "Yesterday, Today, and Tomorrow": "Design Office Named for Mikoyan Victorious"] [Text] The Mikoyan Design Office has won a contract to modernize more than 100 MiG-21 bis fighter planes in the armory of the Indian Air Force. As the Indian Ministry of Defense reported, the contract is valued at $350 million. The Russians won this right in fierce competition with Western and Israeli companies.
